main event: Unidentified flying object reported near Barberton, Ohio on 30 March 1965.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 30,000-40,000 feet.,The observation was made for approximately 1.5 seconds.,The report was forwarded for additional analysis and required further information.,A letter from 20 March 1965 mentions a reddish-orange round object observed for about 30 to 45 minutes.,The investigation is part of the Project Blue Book documentation.
